At first sight it looks like nothing more than a fallen leaf, brittle and brown with a few insect bites taken out.

But closer inspection reveals that the piece of foliage is in fact a cunningly camouflaged insect which has managed to blend in with its jungle surroundings.

Seconds after its hiding place was disturbed, the animal - a sort of grasshopper known as the leaf katydid - spreads its wings to reveal vibrant autumnal patterns on the inside.

