It was noticed by American photographer Piotr Naskrecki, who took the pictures after making the lucky find as he travelled across the continent.

He said: 'If you ever visit a humid, tropical area in South or Central America you may be rewarded with the discovery of one of the most amazing animals - the leaf katydid.

'The only way to notice them is to look for the movement of their long antennae and legs as they slowly munch on leaves at night.'

Mr Naskrecki added: 'These katydids are probably the best mimics of plants among all insects.

