'Their mimicry is by no means restricted to resemblance of plain, green leaves - that would be too easy.

'When the insects fall to the ground, they often play dead when approached by a predator.'

'Their bodies are replicas of leaves that have been chewed up, torn, rotten, dried up, partially decayed, or covered by fungi. But the best part is that no two individuals are alike.'

